********************************************************************************
C MeatAxe Version 2.4                                                     README
********************************************************************************

This is the C MeatAxe, a set of programs for computing with modular
representations. See below for installation instructions.


================================================================================
PACKAGE OVERVIEW
================================================================================

Directory	Contents
----------	--------------------------------------------
bin/		Executables (empty).
src/		Source files.
test/		Test suite.
doc/ 		Documentation in HTML format.



================================================================================
INSTALLATION (for Unix systems)
================================================================================

1) Copy Makefile.conf.dist to Makefile.conf. Edit Makefile.conf
   and fill in the necessary parameters.

2) To compile all programs an run the test suite, enter

	make check

   You will probably need gmake (GNU make) to build the MeatAxe.



